  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6550.36 sitting directly on the max negative gamma strike (-18.2B), dealers are aggressively buying the dip right here, providing temporary support but creating amplified volatility as we're in breakout regime. The thick cluster of negative gamma walls from 6525-6550 means any bounce will face immediate dealer selling pressure, while a break below 6525 opens up more pronounced selling as dealers chase momentum. Watch 6580 as the critical resistance level where max positive gamma (+3.9B) will trigger heavy dealer selling if we rally back toward it.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect violent swings around 6550 with dealers buying dips but selling any meaningful bounce.",
